### Development / Local `.env` for MyRhythmNexus
### IMPORTANT: Do NOT commit real production secrets to this file in a public repo.
### Use a secrets manager (Vault, KeyVault, Railway secrets, environment variables on the host) in production.

## Database
# SQLite example (uncomment for quick local development):
# DATABASE_URL=sqlite+aiosqlite:///./dev.db
# PostgreSQL example (replace user/pass/host/port/db):
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:postgres@localhost:5432/myrhythmnexus

## Initial superuser (development only). In production create the admin via migrations or admin tooling.
FIRST_SUPERUSER=admin@example.com
FIRST_SUPERUSER_PASSWORD=admin123

## License Server (if you run the separate License microservice locally)
# For production/testing against Railway services, set the public license server URL below
RHYTHM_NEXUS_LICENSE_SERVER_URL=https://licenseserver-production-0ceb.up.railway.app/api/v1

# Desktop / client backend base URL (include API base path)
# Example: https://your-app.up.railway.app/api/v1
RHYTHM_NEXUS_BACKEND_URL=https://tugbadansvespor-production.up.railway.app

## Security / Tokens
# Replace with a strong secret in production. Example generator:
# python - <<PY
# import secrets,base64
# print(base64.urlsafe_b64encode(secrets.token_bytes(32)).decode())
# PY
SECRET_KEY=REPLACE_ME_WITH_STRONG_SECRET
ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES=10080

## Server binding
HOST=0.0.0.0
PORT=8000

## CORS origins
# Must be a JSON array so pydantic's BaseSettings can parse it properly.
CORS_ORIGINS=["http://localhost:8000","https://yourdomain.com","app://rhythm-nexus"]

## Optional: logging and debug toggles (development helpers)
# DEBUG=true
# LOG_LEVEL=info

### End of file
